                                   A BILL

To establish a federated commons architecture for land, data, and intellectual
property; to authorize the formation and certification of Qualified Federated
Networks; to provide for Federated Commons Membership and guaranteed material
provisions; to facilitate the transfer of surplus federal land and dual-use
technologies to community-governed trusts; to establish a National Resilience
Ledger and Commons Credit system; to mandate open technical infrastructure
standards for distributed resource coordination; and to provide for the
long-term economic sovereignty and material resilience of the United States
against systemic fragility in global currency and energy markets.

Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives of the United States
of America in Congress assembled,

