SEC. 1107. EFFECTIVE DATE.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

(a) GENERAL EFFECTIVE DATE.-- Except as otherwise provided in this Act, the
provisions of this Act shall take effect on the date of enactment.

(b) DELAYED EFFECTIVE DATES.-- The following provisions shall take effect on the
dates specified:

    (1) the FMOS mandatory adoption requirements of Section 701(b)(1) of Title
    VII of this Act -- three years after the date of enactment for energy
    management, agricultural production, and water management devices;

    (2) the FMOS mandatory adoption requirements of Section 701(b)(2) of Title
    VII of this Act -- four years after the date of enactment for consumer
    electronics and communications infrastructure devices;

    (3) the FMOS mandatory adoption requirements of Section 701(b)(3) of Title
    VII of this Act -- five years after the date of enactment for all other
    networked devices;

    (4) the voluntary commons dedication pathway of Section 506(a)(1) of Title V
    of this Act -- operative immediately upon enactment for all works regardless
    of creation date; and the abandoned-works mechanism of Section 506(a)(2)
    through (5) of this Act -- the one-hundred-eighty-day notice period runs from
    the date of enactment for works already inactive fourteen or more years, and
    from the date the fourteen-year inactivity period is reached for works not yet
    at that threshold; and

    (5) the anti-thicket patent portfolio concentration limit of Section 506(d)
    of Title V of this Act -- the two-year review period for existing portfolios
    begins on the date of enactment, with the concentration limit enforceable
    upon completion of that review.

(c) EXPEDITED EFFECTIVE DATES.-- The following provisions shall take effect on
an expedited basis, reflecting their urgency:

    (1) the DARPA SCORE program transfer of Section 903(e) of Title IX of this
    Act -- ninety days after the date of enactment;

    (2) the Bootstrap Grant Program application portal of Section 1007(a)(2) of
    Title X of this Act -- ninety days after the date of enactment;

    (3) the Proto-QFN recognition of Section 1001 of Title X of this Act --
    immediately upon the date of enactment; and

    (4) the constitutional safe harbor of Section 1101 of this Title --
    immediately upon the date of enactment, retroactive to the date of
    introduction of this Act in Congress.

